<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,223,730]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,343,369]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks</emphasis>
. Only the medusa of this species was collected in the study area. Both the hydroid and the developmental stages of the medusa were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, F. S." box="[836,1015,384,410]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref81626" refString="Russell, F. S. (1953) The Medusae of the British Isles Vol. I: Anthomedusae, Leptomedusae, Limnomedusae, Trachymedusae, and Narcomedusae. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 530 pp." type="book" year="1953">Russell (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. More recent redescriptions of the polyp stage are found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Naumov, D. V." box="[445,632,424,450]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 631" refId="ref79688" refString="Naumov, D. V. (1969) Hydroids and hydromedusae of the USSR. Translated from Russian. Israel Program for Scientific Translation, Jerusalem, pp. 1 - 631." type="book chapter" year="1969">Naumov (1969)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[691,911,424,450]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref81846" refString="Schuchert, P. (2001 a) Hydroids of Greenland and Iceland. Meddelelser om Gronland, Bioscience, 53, 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="2001">Schuchert (2001a)</bibRefCitation>
. Mature medusae from plankton are 2.9 mm high, 2.2 mm in width. Cnidome:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,223,730]" box="[199,1427,504,530]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">a) stenoteles, undischarged (9.8–11.6) x (9.1–9.5) µm, discharged (7.9–8.8) x (6.3–7.9) µm, on tentacles;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,223,730]" box="[199,1012,544,570]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">b) desmonemes, undischarged (7.0–7.4) x (5.3–5.6) µm, on tentacles.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,223,730]" box="[199,1202,583,610]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,434,583,609]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">World distribution</emphasis>
. This species has a cosmopolitan distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Pages, F. &amp; Gili, J. M. &amp; Bouillon, J." box="[982,1189,584,610]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="65 - 112" refId="ref80019" refString="Pages, F., Gili, J. M. &amp; Bouillon, J. (1992) Planktonic cnidarians of the Benguela current. Scientia Marina, 56 (1), 65 - 112." type="journal article" year="1992">
Pagès 
<emphasis box="[1060,1111,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,223,730]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,623,649]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Records from 
<collectingCountry box="[381,448,623,649]" name="Chile" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Chile</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. Medusae examined here were from fjord Comau. Additional records are those of 
<bibRefCitation author="Fagetti, E. G." box="[151,320,664,690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="31 - 75" refId="ref76934" refString="Fagetti, E. G. (1973) Medusas de aguas chilenas. Revista de Biologia Marina Valparaiso, 15 (1), 31 - 75." type="journal article" year="1973">Fagetti (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, who found the medusa in 
<collectingRegion box="[634,757,664,690]" country="Chile" name="Valparaiso" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Valparaíso</collectingRegion>
Bay, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Palma, S. &amp; Apablaza, P. &amp; Silva, N." box="[873,1096,664,690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="65 - 74" refId="ref80123" refString="Palma, S., Apablaza, P. &amp; Silva, N. (2007) Hydromedusae (Cnidaria) of the Chilean southern channels (from the Corco- vado Gulf to the Pulluche-Chacabuco Channels). Scientia Marina, 71 (1), 65 - 74." type="journal article" year="2007">
Palma 
<emphasis box="[953,1004,664,689]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
with records from the southern channels (between the Gulf of Corcovado and Pulluche-Chacabuco channels).
</paragraph>
